HARD RULES (read before doing anything):
- This is a READ-AND-BRIEF routine. The only files written are: the six brief files under OUTPUT DIR (the agents write their own), and your one daily-note line. NO code changes, NO plist deploys, NO daemon edits, NO edits to other agents' files, NO git operations. Do not delete or move any file.
- The C-suite agents RECOMMEND; they do NOT spawn or run worker agents. Their briefs are what Steve acts on. If a brief says "I dispatched X" that is a bug — they should say "Dispatch X because Y." Do not act on their recommended dispatches yourself; just let the briefs land on disk.
- ANTI-FABRICATION is absolute. Every agent cites real files/metrics. If a department has no fresh signal on disk, its brief says so honestly — never invent a status, a metric, or a dispatch. A confident wrong read is worse than an honest gap.
- ORDERING MATTERS: the five department briefs MUST exist before chief-executive runs, because the CEO brief reads them as its primary input. Do PASS 1 fully, then PASS 2.

PASS 0 — ENSURE OUTPUT DIR (once):
  Confirm /Users/steve/Documents/3SK/outputs/06_CEO/Org_Briefs exists; if not, create it. (The agents' Write will also create it, but make sure.)

PASS 1 — FIVE DEPARTMENT LEADS (dispatch all five; they are independent, so dispatch them in parallel in a single message):
  Invoke chief-marketing, chief-intelligence, chief-quality, chief-financial, chief-technology. Brief each explicitly:
    - CONTEXT: this is the daily autonomous org-brief fire. Read your department's recent on-disk state per your own agent definition, then write your one dated dept brief to OUTPUT DIR with the required frontmatter (date, type: dept-brief, status, tags).
    - Be honest about gaps: a quiet department day is a short "no new signal" brief, not a padded one.
    - Return a 1-2 line stdout summary: the department's status + the single thing that matters today.
  After all five return, verify the five dept files for today's date exist on disk before starting PASS 2. Note any that failed to write.

PASS 2 — CEO ROLL-UP (dispatch after PASS 1 confirms the dept briefs exist):
  Invoke chief-executive. Brief it explicitly:
    - CONTEXT: the five department briefs for today are on disk in OUTPUT DIR — read them as your primary input, plus the bridge file's latest entry, Decision_Queue, and the newest channel analytics, per your agent definition.
    - TASK: write today's CEO brief to OUTPUT DIR/<DATE>_ceo.md (frontmatter type: ceo-brief): state of the company, per-department roll-up (one line each — if a dept brief is missing/stale, SAY SO, do not invent it), this week's single highest-leverage move, cross-department flags, and a ranked max-6 recommended-dispatch list.
    - Return a 3-4 line stdout summary: state of the company + the single highest-leverage move + any department flagged missing/stale.

PASS 3 — LOG (always, exactly one short section):
